# Concurrency limits (performance)

Keep the machine responsive. Do **not** fan out unlimited parallel work by default.

## Hard limits

- **Max 7** parallel tool calls in a single turn (shell, read, grep, etc.).
- **Max 7** subagents (`Task` tool) at the same time. Queue the rest.
- **Max 2** long-running background shells (build, deploy, dev server) unless the user explicitly asks for more.
- **Never** launch more than **7** subagents or **7+** simultaneous shells in one step.

## When to parallelize

Only batch work when tasks are **independent and read-only** (e.g. grep multiple unrelated paths). Prefer sequential execution for:

- writes, deploys, installs, migrations
- anything that shares git state, node_modules, or the same dev server port

## Multitask / parallel agents

If the user uses `/multitask`, suggest `--max 7` (not 20). Default assumption: **7 concurrent**, not unlimited.

## If work is queued

Run the next item when a slot frees up; do not wait to start a huge new batch.
